  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "This was brought up by @protolambda. We are inconsistent on the handling of `fork_version`:\r\n\r\n* We define it as a `uint64`.\r\n* We use it as a `uint32` when doing `fork_version * 2**32 + domain_type`.\r\n\r\nI think it would be cleaner if the final signing logic used `hash(message_hash + bytes8(fork_version) + byte1(domain))` as opposed to `hash(message_hash + bytes8(domain))`.",
