    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "A clean solution (idea taken from @vbuterin) is to define `fork_version` as a `byte[4]`. It also makes more sense semantically because we're doing no arithmetic on it. We can also define `domain_type` as a `byte[4]`, which again makes more sense semantically. We then replace `return fork_version * 2**32 + domain_type` with `return fork_version + domain_type`.",
